title: Intel finally details its 12th-gen P- and U-series chips for ultrabooks and foldables
content:
At CES this year, Intel’s focus was on chips for gaming laptops, but it did unveil the SKUs of its new 12th-gen P- and U-series processors, which are going to be in new ultrabooks, convertibles, foldables, and more.
